# Stacked density plot

If you want to create a stacked density plot, you probably want to `'count'` (density * n) variable instead of the default density.

Following plot loses marginal densities:

<pre class="mcode">
p <-    
 ggplot(diamonds, aes(carat, fill = cut)) +
  geom_density(position = "stack")
  
plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>
